                                    <p>Accidental damage is when something happens to your phone that is entirely out of your control.</p>
                                    <p>Usually, it is something that other insurance companies try to add-on to your existing plan for an extra fee - which is pretty weird - how can you be expected to prevent something that is out of your control?</p>
                                    <p>Examples of accidental damage:</p>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Spillages: this is one of the most common causes of an accidental damage claim. You would think that people would stop dropping their phones in pints, but they never seem to learn.</li>
